      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "To maximize mechanical tension, you should focus on lifting heavy weights with controlled movements, generally favoring lower repetitions in the 5-12 rep range. This high load creates significant strain on the muscle fibers, which is the key signal. Cellulary, this tension causes microscopic damage to the muscle fibers, prompting them to initiate repair and adapt by growing stronger and larger. Think about maximizing time under tension while maintaining heavy loads.",
