    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense. so when you say it's because of those microscopic changes and the cells reacting to the weight... how does that actually work internally? like what's the actual mechanism that translates that physical pull into the muscle actually getting bigger? is it just a chemical reaction or is something more active happening inside the fibers?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The translation from physical pull to size involves signaling cascades within the muscle cells. When high tension is applied, it activates mechanosensors within the muscle fibers, which send signals to the cell nucleus. This signaling cascade increases the activity of anabolic pathways, most notably the mTOR pathway. mTOR activation essentially tells the muscle cell to synthesize more proteins than it breaks down, leading to an increase in muscle protein synthesis and subsequent hypertrophy.",
      "source": "target",
